**[1862, 09-23] Ms.B.1.6.9.46**

May Jr. to RDW

Reports about Emancipation Proclamation {Some in {u}BAA{/u}.} He is
filled more with gratitude than with regret over the slowness of the
measure. He thinks there is a slim danger of becoming a military
despotism because of the administration’s kowtowing to military
expediency, but he is confident that the virtue of the Union’s soldiers
and the Northern people will not let that happen.


